The Tunisian man thought to be responsible for the deadly truck attack was shot dead on 23 December by Italian police. BERLIN - Dutch police said on Wednesday they were investigating whether the man believed responsible for last week's deadly Christmas market attack in Berlin may have travelled through the Netherlands.Twelve people died in the 19 December attack. The Tunisian suspect, 24-year-old Anis Amri, was shot dead on 23 December by Italian police. Wim de Bruin, spokesman for the National Prosecutor's Office, said there were &quot;signs&quot; Amri had passed through the Netherlands on his way to France, and an investigation was ongoing.WATCH: Berlin attack: Isis claims it inspired truck assault at market